Professeure qui connait sa matière sur le bout de ses doigts. Accessible, amicale et aidante, elle désire aider les étudiants dans leur apprentissage. Bien que son cours soit très exigeant en effort et en temps, il est très payant de l'avoir comme professeure puisque j'ai énormément appris avec elle. Elle répond aux questions de curiosité.

Immersion student here, Pass/fail this course the second you can. DO NOT even think about getting anything over a C+ in her class. The prof constantly goes off topic and is very rude towards students. If you do not understand something she insults your intelligenceshe expects u to read 100's of pages per week of academic french. MUST AVOID

I'm only in 1st year and this class was misery. The prof's lectures are long, off topic and boring, the readings are like a flood on which there is a late-semester test on ALL of them and the readings are long, dense and hard to understand especially if you're not native French. If you see this course, run the other way.

The class is so boring and hard to understand. She gives you at least 4 difficult readings to do per week and at the end of the semester there's a quiz on all of them. Plus, she assigns group projects and barely gives any directions for them. She needs to understand that this is only a 1st year class.

Le professeur ne se rend pas compte que ce n'est pas tout le monde qui aime la politique ou qui a envie de poursuivre dans ce domaine. Ce n'est pas une maîtrise! La majorité n'a pas le choix de prendre ce cours. Elle doit donc apprendre à être plus flexible dans sa manière d'enseigner. Sans compter qu'IL Y A BEAUCOUP DE LECTURES!!! Je n'exagère pas
The lectures are very boring and the assigned reading is much too technical for a first year class.

Worse prof I've had during my undergrad. Not approachable at all and very little space for you to think. If you don't repeat exactly what she says then you'll easily get a C. Got a B+ in that class and I've never worked that much for any other courses. Sadly, given her background with some NGO's and One Drop I thought she'd be great. Avoid class

While the exams and assignments were difficult in nature, with every lecture she emoted passion for the subject. You can tell that she really knows what she's talking about. She brought in some really interesting and relevant speakers, as well as held seminars outside of class for those who were interested in a little more.

Très bonne prof. La matière est extrêmement abstraite. Pour aimer ce cours il faut adorer la politique et n'en manger. Ce cours donne un aperçu général de plusieurs autres cours de science politique selon Paquerot. Elle est quand même très inspirante comme prof.
Lectures can be long because the material is abstract. Although you can tell she loves what she's teaching. Doing the readings are almost essential.

The expectations for this class are extremely high. She assigns 3 group projects and barely provides help with them. The readings are very difficult and then she has a test at the end of the semester on each reading. There are minimum 2 per class. This is a very hard course to follow if French is not your first language. Try to avoid if possible.

If you have time on in your schedule to read 2 hours of text per night as an immersion student in an immersion level class, enjoy! Most of them were written from Universities in France and are really not relevant in lectures but somehow your mark depends on their understanding.  She gets off topic quickly and I always left early due to relevancy.
